                            <comment id="469536" author="rread" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2025 15:50:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be good if &lt;tt&gt;recv()&lt;/tt&gt; could return multiple records. &#160;Also would be nice to have an &#160;&quot;auto clear&quot; option in &lt;tt&gt;start()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160; so previous records are cleared on each fetch, or something like that. &#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="469376" author="rread" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2025 22:04:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;user&quot; is an overloaded term and may suggest more than what this actually is, which is the simply the name of a consumer.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So how about we call these &quot;consumers&quot;, instead? That makes it clear that when a consumer is created with register, then it should also be actually consuming logs. &#160;And the fn names could be along the lines of &lt;tt&gt;llapi_cl_consumer_start()&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;llapi_cl_consumer_clear()&lt;/tt&gt;, etc. This puts more emphasis on the most important thing - this a changelog &lt;em&gt;consumer&lt;/em&gt; interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
